					<h3>Help Your Employees Reduce Their Carbon Footprints by Greening Their Deliveries</h3>
					<p>Shopping online and sending deliveries to a KinekPoint doesn't just save employees time; it can also help reduce their carbon footprint. Here are just three ways that using Kinek and shopping online can help green employee deliveries:</p>
					
					<br /><br />
					
					<img src="resource/images/green/greeningcorporate_reducefuelconsumption.jpg" width="68" height="53" alt="Reduce fuel consumption" class="floatRight" />
					<p><strong>Reduce fuel consumption.</strong> When your employees shop online, they avoid driving around town and spending time in an idling car. Less parking spaces and traffic congestion means more green spaces.</p>
					
					<br /><br />
					
					<img src="resource/images/green/greeningcorporate_lessenergy.jpg" width="129" height="66" alt="Fewer goods shipped means less energy used" class="floatLeft" />
					<p><strong>Fewer goods shipped means less energy used.</strong> When your employees shop online, only the items they decide to purchase are shipped from the manufacturer (as opposed to the overstocking and returning of items that traditional retailers have to deal with).</p>
					
					<br /><br />
					
					<img src="resource/images/green/greeningcorporate_cleanerair.jpg" width="102" height="95" alt="Cleaner air in employee neighborhoods" class="floatRight" />
					<p><strong>Cleaner air in employee neighborhoods.</strong> When people in and around an employee's neighborhood all ship to a KinekPoint, they reduce the number of miles delivery trucks have to travel. Fewer stops means less fuel consumption and, since someone will always be at a KinekPoint to accept your employee's parcel, there are no repeat delivery attempts.</p>
					
					<br /><br />
					
