						<h3>Did you know..?</h3>
						<p>When UPS reduced left hand turns in 2007, the impact on the environment was undeniable. This one change shaved almost <strong>30 million miles</strong> from delivery routes and resulted in a <strong>savings of 3 million gallons of gas</strong>. The reduction of emissions was equivalent to <strong>removing 5,300 passenger cars from the road</strong> for one year.*</p>
						<p><small>Source: UPS Public Relations (<a href="http://pressroom.ups.com/Fact+Sheets/UPS+Avoids+Left+Turns+to+Save+Fuel%2C+Reduce+Emissions+and+Improve+Safety" title="view fact sheet" target="_blank">view fact sheet</a>)</small></p>
					
						<h3>Imagine...</h3>
